Interview Explanation (5 Simple Points)
A tree is balanced if the height difference between the left and right subtree of every node is at most 1.
I use DFS to calculate the height of each subtree.
At every node, I check abs(leftHeight - rightHeight).
If the difference is greater than 1, I return -1 to indicate the tree is not balanced.
If no node returns -1, the tree is balanced. Time complexity is O(n) because each node is visited only once.
Easy Memory Trick
Height = 1 + max(left, right)

Check = abs(left - right) <= 1

If difference > 1 → return -1

If height() != -1 → Balanced
Time Complexity
Time: O(n)
Space: O(h) (recursive stack, where h is the tree height)
